dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma run out (†Sangakkara/Jayawardene) 69 (73b 7x4 0x6 118m) SR: 94.52

dismissalComment.html: all over. Rohit is run out trying to keep strike. Full and wide outside off, but this time he does not middle the lofted square drive.. It dribbles down to third man, and Rohit runs back desperate to keep strike. Razor-sharp throw from Mahela, I reckon - Sanga had little to do, as Rohit jumped inside in an attempt to make his crease.. but the bails were already off. India have collapsed in bizarre fashion here.

dismissalText.commentary: MS Dhoni run out (Kapugedera) 41 (53b 6x4 0x6 59m) SR: 77.35

dismissalComment.html: wicket against the run of play, and a huge one! Dhoni is run out. Tapped with soft hands straight to point, and Rohit calls Dhoni across for a tight single.. he hares down to the non-striker's end but is beaten easily by Kapugedera, swooping in from point and letting rip an arrow-throw to the non-striker's end.

headshotImage.caption: Farveez Maharoof player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Farveez Maharoof player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: he's a goner this time! Maharoof keeps it outside off, moved away ever so slightly from off stump and it was enough to fox Kohli, and get the edge as he prodded unconvincingly off the back foot. Sangakkara leaps in joy after pouching it, and that's another failure for Kohli in the Asia Cup.

and he's gone first ball, playing all around a straight ball like a deer caught in the headlights! Jadeja walked across to the off stump for some reason and missed a ball headed for middle stump. India have lost two in two.

headshotImage.caption: Praveen Kumar, player page headshot cutout 2022
headshotImage.longCaption: Praveen Kumar, player page headshot cutout 2022

dismissalComment.html: Team hat-trick! Maharoof has gone past Praveen Kumar first ball, as he looked to play a nothing-shot to a ball not too short and far too close to off stump. The inside edge falls on the stumps and Maharoof is now on a hat-trick all of his own!

headshotImage.caption: Zaheer Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Zaheer Khan player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: AND HE'S DONE IT! Rangiri Dambulla comes alive, as Zaheer Khan outside edges a ball that was doing nothing special, except that it was pitched on off.. Zaheer got forward and poked without much conviction and the outside edge flew wide of Sangakkara, who dives to his right and plucked it.. Four in four for SL.. Maharoof who made an unexpected comeback for the Asia Cup is the man of the moment.

and Maharoof has another one! Superb yorker, tailing in on leg stump and Dinda plays a questionable swipe off the back foot instead of guarding his castle.. He misses, Maharoof hits and India are nine down! Maharoof has a five-for!

headshotImage.caption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Dinesh Karthik player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: whoa! Billy Bowden sets a record for a late decision, that would have made Steve Bucknor proud! Superb bowling from Herath, spin and bounce from middle, ripping across Karthik. Did it take the edge on the way to Sangakkara? Sri Lanka thought so, and around 10 seconds later, so did Billy who raised the crooked finger. Karthik goes in the 40s again.

whoa! A tight call there but the right one and Raina has to go! That was speared in from wide of the crease, from round the wicket, Raina goes for the sweep and misses as it straightens. Hits him in front of middle and off. Umpire Oxenford rules it out after thinking hard and long. Big wicket - pitched on leg and would have hit the top of middle.

dismissalText.commentary: Gautam Gambhir c Randiv b Mathews 23 (31b 3x4 0x6 52m) SR: 74.19

dismissalComment.html: Suraj Randiv take a bow! Catch of the tournament! He did this once before, diving to his right to save a boundary, but this time he's stopped Gambhir's innings. That was short and asking for punishment, Gambhir obliged by opening up his stance and whack-pulling it with ferocity well to the right of Randiv at short midwicket... but in the air. Randiv dived across full length and itercepted it mid-air, fully horizontal to pluck it one-handed. Classy.

commentTextItems.html: Mahela has had enough of this nonsense and slog-sweeps from outside off to midwicket. Fifty to Mahela and victory to Sri Lanka.

commentPostTextItems.html: They have got a bonus point, but more importantly they have got the right morale boost ahead of the big game. Forget the trends from the past, Sri Lanka will go in as favourites. India's bowling looked ordinary today, and while Harbhajan will lift the standards considerably, there is enough cause for concern. India's collapse with the bat was bizarre, and even more worrying - this is the same batting line up that will play in the finals.

Shruti: "The first match of the series between SL and Pak match tried to successfully justify the existence of ODIs, however the rest of the matches in the series have more or less tried to kill any such notions...(except India-Pak I guess!)"

Dhoni: "Well of course, we got off to a decent start.. 160 odd on the board with six wickets in hand, we were looking at 270 odd, but Maharoof came on and turned it around completely. We did not have much chance after that. We have done well so far, batsmen have got runs. Would have been nice to carry confidence into the final, but unfortunately that did not happen. Finals in a couple of days.. we have to work on the areas where we can improve."

Sangakkara: "Very happy with the fact that we won so well in the end. Kapugedera's run out (of Dhoni) turned it around, and then Maharoof's hat-trick, what can you say! We just tried a new combination today, and I'm very happy with the way they performed. We have got to do it again in the finals. This win gives us confidence, but the finals is a finals. We have to start from scratch. It was pretty good to chase under lights today.. probably easier to bat during the day.."

Maharoof is as expected the Man of the Match for his five-for inclusive of that hat-trick. "I've done really well through the series.. hard work has paid off - Dambulla has always been lucky to me. To be honest, I had not planned for the hat-trick. Just wanted to keep it in good areas and it worked. In Dambulla when you hit that line and length there is always something for the bowlers. Sangakkara took a marvellous catch to give me the hat-trick, really happy for the team."
On that happy note we will wrap up the coverage for this game. Do tune in for the finals in a couple of days. On behalf of Team Cricinfo, this is Nitin Sundar signing off. Cheers!

commentTextItems.html: much ado about nothing. Mahela cuts uppishly, the fielder at point could not get there in time as it landed safely, but the throw came in to the non-striker's end as Kandamby ran back. It hit the stumps, but he was just in.
late cut goes straight to the fielder behind square on the off side
deliberately padded to the off side. I haven't seen that in an ODI for a while. Mahela's fifty is on the platter now, ready to be devoured.

headshotImage.caption: Pragyan Ojha player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Pragyan Ojha player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: now to the on side. Yawn.

commentPreTextItems.html: Sri Lanka have ripped India today. Yes tis was a second-string India side, but Sri Lanka were third-string to be honest. They rested four of their first-choice players, while India rested three from the squad currently in Dambulla. There too, it is up for debate if Ashish Nehra can be termed first-choice.

commentTextItems.html: defends to the off side. Soporific stuff.
tossed up on leg stump, played down to the off side
rank long hop, pulled without timing to the deep. Two more.
ah, rapped on the pads by an armer angling in. There is an appeal, but its turned down and runs away for four
worked off the pads to midwicket who tumbles and fumbles. Kandamby runs across for two

headshotImage.caption: Pragyan Ojha player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Pragyan Ojha player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: tossed up outside off and driven easily to sweeper cover
arm ball coming in, Mahela gets forward and defends
Single! Whoop! To the covers off the outside edge
again, played into the covers. SL don't seem to want the pointless Bonus point. Can India still give them one?

commentPreTextItems.html: Jadeja the allrounder (within quotes) comes on.

commentTextItems.html: Kandamby leans forward and defends down the track
straightens from leg stump, Mahela again gets forward and blocks.

commentPostTextItems.html: Even by SL-India standards, this is a real drag now.

dismissalText.commentary: Zaheer Khan c †Sangakkara b Maharoof 0 (1b 0x4 0x6 1m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: AND HE'S DONE IT! Rangiri Dambulla comes alive, as Zaheer Khan outside edges a ball that was doing nothing special, except that it was pitched on off.. Maharoof who made an unexpected comeback for the Asia Cup is the man of the moment.

dismissalComment.html: Suraj Randiv take a bow! Catch of the tournament! He did this once before, diving to his right to save a boundary, but this time he's stopped Gambhir's innings. That was short and asking for punishment, Gambhir obliged by opening up his stance and whack-pulling it with ferocity well to the right of Randiv at short midwicket... but in the air. Randiv dived across full length and itercepted it mid-air, fully horizontal to pluck it one-handed. Classy.

Did it take the edge on the way to Sangakkara? Sri Lanka thought so, and around 10 seconds later, so did Billy who raised the crooked finger. Karthik goes in the 40s again.

whoa! A tight call there but the right one and Raina has to go! That was speared in from wide of the crease, from round the wicket, Raina goes for the sweep and misses as it straightens. Hits him in front of middle and off. Umpire Oxenford rules it out after thinking hard and long. Big wicket - pitched on leg and would have hit the top of middle.

dismissalText.commentary: Rohit Sharma run out (†Sangakkara/Jayawardene) 69 (73b 7x4 0x6 118m) SR: 94.52

dismissalComment.html: all over. Rohit is run out trying to keep strike. Full and wide outside off, but this time he does not middle the lofted square drive.. It dribbles down to third man, and Rohit runs back desperate to keep strike. Razor-sharp throw from Mahela, I reckon - Sanga had little to do, as Rohit jumped inside in an attempt to make his crease.. but the bails were already off. India have collapsed in bizarre fashion here.

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga c †Dhoni b Khan 38 (46b 6x4 0x6 57m) SR: 82.6

dismissalComment.html: Zaheer roars having finally got rid of Tharanga after having troubled him for a while. Short of a length outside off, nothing special about that ball, but that's like saying there was nothing special about Glenn McGrath. Tharanga again pokes uncertainly, and inevitably he's edged one. Dhoni does the rest.

dismissalComment.html: India strike with some smart field placement! Short ball, challenges Dilshan to spull and he obliges, but can't keep it along the ground and it carries straight to deep midwicket. Against the run of play, India have struck.

stories.summary: Three wickets for 19 runs stalled India's start, and then Farveez Maharoof's hat-trick destroyed the middle order's rebuild and practically finished the dress rehearsal for the final in Sri Lanka's favour
